pdnIfExtEncapConfig.description: This Mib is created to facilitate configuration of interface related objects.

PdnLinkRole.name: PdnLinkRole
PdnLinkRole.description: Objects defined with this textual convention are used to indicate the usage of the link. uplink (1) : interface is used as uplink other (2) : interface is used for something other than uplink (e.g, subtending).

pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapConfigTable.name: pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapConfigTable
pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapConfigTable.description: This table that contains additional interface configuration information.

pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapConfigEntry.name: pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapConfigEntry
pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapConfigEntry.description: There will be one of these rows for each interface that supports RFC1483.

pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapConfigIPRoutedPDU.name: pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapConfigIPRoutedPDUs
pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapConfigIPRoutedPDU.description: In the upstream direction user can configure the IP routed PDUs in the LLC SNAP encapsulation or VC Based Multiplexing encapsulation (RFC1483). If neither is configured 'none' is used. The direction is determined by the transmit direction. Initialy this object was developed for the endpoint use where the transmit direction is upstream. This object could be used for CO type equipment where the direction would be downstream.

pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapConfigBridgedPDUs.name: pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapConfigBridgedPDUs
pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapConfigBridgedPDUs.description: In the transmit direction user can configure the IP routed PDUs in the LLC SNAP encapsulation or VC Based Multiplexing encapsulation (RFC1483). If neither is configured 'none' is used.

pdnIfXLinkConfigTable.name: pdnIfXLinkConfigTable
pdnIfXLinkConfigTable.description: This table contains configuration information for interfaces that are capable of switch roles at run-time.

pdnIfXLinkConfigEntry.name: pdnIfXLinkConfigEntry
pdnIfXLinkConfigEntry.description: An entry in this table represents an interface that is capable of being used as an uplink. Typically, this table will contain entries only for interfaces that are capable of switching roles.

pdnIfXLinkConfigRole.name: pdnIfXLinkConfigRole
pdnIfXLinkConfigRole.description: This object allows users to configure the role (e.g., uplink) intended for this interface.

pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapCompliance.name: pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapCompliance
pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which support RFC1483 Multiprotocol Encapsulation over ATM adaptation layer 5.

pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapsulationOptionalG.name: pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapsulationOptionalGroup
pdnIfMultiprotocolEncapsulationOptionalG.description: A collection of objects providing optional configuration information about multiprotocol interface link.

pdnIfXLinkConfigOptionalGroup.name: pdnIfXLinkConfigOptionalGroup
pdnIfXLinkConfigOptionalGroup.description: configuration information for this optional group.
